## Skill 3: Notion Sync

**Trigger:** Loop 2 completion, phase milestone, session end.

### Notion Database IDs (canonical)
| Surface | Collection URL |
|---|---|
| Task Tracker | `collection://a74e62ce-09da-455d-b2ee-7ade3d89ff47` |
| Feature Tracker | `collection://c357977b-4718-4ce1-97d9-971f70c86ba1` |
| Decision Log | `collection://b10e204a-78f4-43c7-9aab-6fb25eb44203` |
| Phase Progress | `collection://824857c4-a1f6-4cd3-9d8a-5520d533aca7` |
| Session Log | `collection://1b7a295a-6427-44c4-9bcd-00b9f03692a0` |
| Project Hub | `https://www.notion.so/33613205fce68182a043cc6ad0088c3e` |

### Sync Sequence (session end)
1. Task Tracker: completed tasks → Done; new tasks added with all required fields
2. Feature Tracker: status updated for features that progressed this session
3. Decision Log: new ADRs added (Status = Accepted, Summary, Date)
4. Session Log: new entry added — mandatory every session, no exception
5. Hub callout: update with current state string
6. Phase Progress: update if phase milestone reached

### Hub Callout Format
```
[Phase X] active. [Task ID] [status]. Branch: `[branch-name]`. Build: ✅/⚠️/❌ | Notion sync: ✅/❌ | Updated: YYYY-MM-DD
```

### System Health Validation (before sync close)
- Task Tracker → Invalid Tasks view = 0 rows
- Feature Tracker → Invalid Features view = 0 rows
- Active Blockers view matches blockers listed in `TASKS.md`

### Ownership
Claude is the sole agent with Notion write access.
Executors never touch Notion. Human may update as directed by Claude.
